thread.title: El Portal route into Yosemite reopens after storm-triggered mudslide
thread.title_full: El Portal route into Yosemite reopens after storm-triggered mudslide - Winnipeg Free Press

author: The Associated Press
title: El Portal route into Yosemite reopens after storm-triggered mudslide
text:
YOSEMITE NATIONAL PARK, Calif. - The El Portal Road route into Yosemite National Park has reopened after clean-up of storm damage.
A park press release says the popular route reopened Thursday evening but that intermittent traffic delays are possible.
El Portal Road had been closed since Tuesday after heavy rains in the Sierra Nevada caused mud and debris flows.
El Portal is a continuation of State Route 140.
